.TH STEGX 1 "April 2026" "stegx 2.0.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
stegx \- authenticated LSB steganography with Argon2id and AES\-GCM

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B stegx
.RI [ global-options ]
.I subcommand
.RI [ options ]
.PP
.B stegx encode
.B \-i
.I COVER
.B \-f
.I FILE
.B \-o
.I OUT.png
.RI [ encode-options ]
.br
.B stegx decode
.B \-i
.I STEGO
.RB { \-d
.I OUT_DIR
.RB |
.B \-\-stdout
.RB |
.B \-d \-
.RB }
.RI [ decode-options ]
.br
.B stegx shamir\-split
.B \-k
.I K
.B \-n
.I N
.B \-f
.I FILE
.B \-c
.I COVER...
.B \-O
.I OUT_DIR
.RI [ encode-options ]
.br
.B stegx shamir\-combine
.B \-i
.I STEGO...
.B \-d
.I OUT_DIR
.RI [ \-o
.IR FILENAME ]
.RI [ decode-options ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B stegx
hides files inside PNG images using password\-shuffled LSB embedding and
authenticated encryption. The payload is compressed with a
multi\-algorithm compressor, encrypted under AES\-256\-GCM (optionally
layered with ChaCha20\-Poly1305), framed in a versioned container whose
header is bound as AEAD associated data, and distributed across the
cover's pixel channels in an order determined by a password\-derived
Argon2id key.
.PP
Version 2 replaces the v1 format entirely. v2 readers can still decrypt
v1 stego images via a fallback path, but v2 stego images are not
backwards\-compatible with 1.x.

.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Print the program version and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Enable debug\-level logging to stderr.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show a help message and exit. Each subcommand also supports \fB\-h\fR.

.SH SUBCOMMANDS

.SS stegx encode
Hide a file inside a cover image and write a stego PNG.
.TP
.BI \-i \ COVER
Cover image. A local path (PNG / BMP / etc.) or an \fBhttp://\fR /
\fBhttps://\fR URL (size\-ceiling 50\ MiB, Content\-Type \fIimage/*\fR,
verified with Pillow, auto\-deleted after use).
.TP
.BI \-f \ FILE
Path to the file to hide.
.TP
.BI \-o \ OUT.png
Output stego image. Non\-PNG extensions are coerced to \fI.png\fR for
lossless LSB storage.
.TP
.BI \-p \ PASSWORD
Password. \fBDiscouraged\fR because it appears in shell history and in
\fI/proc/<pid>/cmdline\fR (visible via \fBps\fR(1)). Prefer the
interactive prompt (default) or \fB\-\-password\-stdin\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-password\-stdin
Read the password from a single line on stdin.
.TP
.BI \-\-keyfile \ PATH
Mix an external binary (e.g. a hardware\-token dump) into the KDF
input, acting as a second factor.
.TP
.BR "\-\-kdf " { argon2id | pbkdf2 }
Password\-based KDF (default: \fBargon2id\fR).
.TP
.B \-\-dual\-cipher
Layer ChaCha20\-Poly1305 on top of AES\-256\-GCM with independent keys
for defence in depth.
.TP
.B \-\-adaptive
Embed only in high\-edge\-cost regions (Laplacian edges) to resist
CNN\-based steganalysers.
.TP
.BI \-\-adaptive\-cutoff \ FLOAT
Percentile cutoff for the edge\-cost filter (0\-1, default 0.40).
.TP
.B \-\-matrix\-embedding
Use F5\-style Hamming(7,3) matrix embedding for the ciphertext body.
Reduces the per\-bit change rate by roughly 2.3x.
.TP
.BI \-\-max\-fill \ PCT
Refuse payloads that would fill more than \fIPCT\fR percent of cover
capacity (default 25.0). Above that threshold modern steganalysers win
reliably.
.TP
.B \-\-strict\-password
Reject passwords with a zxcvbn score below 3, instead of warning.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-preserve\-cover
Do not match the cover's PNG encoder parameters (compress level) on
save.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-compress
Disable compression of the hidden file.
.TP
.BR \-\-compression " {" fast | best }
Compression profile (default \fBbest\fR). \fBfast\fR uses zlib only.
\fBbest\fR tries zlib\-9, LZMA2\-extreme, bzip2\-9, zstd\-22 and
brotli\-11 in parallel and stores the smallest.
.TP
.BI \-\-decoy\-file \ PATH
Hide a second (\fIdecoy\fR) payload alongside the real one for plausible
deniability. Real and decoy occupy disjoint cover regions; either
password unlocks only its own region.
.TP
.BI \-\-decoy\-password \ PASSWORD
Password for the decoy payload (prompted if omitted).

.SS stegx decode
Extract a hidden file from a stego image.
.TP
.BI \-i \ STEGO
Stego image to decode.
.TP
.BI \-d \ OUT_DIR
Directory to write the extracted file. Use \fI\-\fR to pipe to stdout
(equivalent to \fB\-\-stdout\fR).
.TP
.B \-\-stdout
Write the decrypted payload to stdout instead of to a file. Useful for
piping into another program without touching disk. Diagnostics still
go to stderr.
.TP
.BI \-p \ PASSWORD
Password. See note under \fBencode\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-password\-stdin
Read the password from stdin.
.TP
.BI \-\-keyfile \ PATH
Keyfile that was used during encoding; required if the stego image was
produced with \fB\-\-keyfile\fR.

.SS stegx shamir\-split
Split a secret file into \fIn\fR Shamir shares and embed each share in
a separate cover image. Any \fIk\fR of the resulting stego images
reconstruct the secret. Accepts every option documented for
\fBencode\fR in addition to:
.TP
.BI \-k \ K
Threshold: minimum number of shares required to reconstruct the
secret.
.TP
.BI \-n \ N
Total number of shares to produce, with 1 <= k <= n <= 255.
.TP
.BI \-f \ FILE
Secret file.
.TP
.BR \-c \ COVER...
One cover image per share (exactly \fIn\fR required).
.TP
.BI \-O \ OUT_DIR
Directory to write \fIstego_share_XX.png\fR files into.

.SS stegx shamir\-combine
Recover a secret from \fIk\fR or more stego shares.
.TP
.BR \-i \ STEGO...
Stego shares (\fIk\fR or more).
.TP
.BI \-d \ OUT_DIR
Output directory.
.TP
.BI \-o \ FILENAME
Filename for the recovered secret (default: \fIrecovered_secret.bin\fR).
.TP
.BI \-p \ PASSWORD
Password used when splitting.
.TP
.B \-\-password\-stdin
Read the password from stdin.
.TP
.BI \-\-keyfile \ PATH
Keyfile used when splitting (if any).

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Any failure -- missing files, wrong password, wrong keyfile, corrupted
stego, insufficient capacity, invalid arguments, or any other error.
All decode failure modes report the same generic error message; check
\fB\-\-verbose\fR output for diagnostic detail.

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Interactive encode with default hardening:
.RS
.nf
stegx encode \-i landscape.png \-f secret.pdf \-o out.png
.fi
.RE
.PP
Cover pulled straight from a URL:
.RS
.nf
stegx encode \-i https://i.example.com/abc.png \\
      \-f secret.zip \-o out.png
.fi
.RE
.PP
Hardened profile (dual cipher + adaptive + matrix + keyfile):
.RS
.nf
stegx encode \-i cover.png \-f secret.bin \-o out.png \\
      \-\-dual\-cipher \-\-adaptive \\
      \-\-matrix\-embedding \-\-keyfile token.bin
.fi
.RE
.PP
Plausible\-deniability decoy:
.RS
.nf
stegx encode \-i cover.png \-f real.zip \-o out.png \\
      \-\-decoy\-file harmless.txt
.fi
.RE
.PP
Decode straight into another tool without touching disk:
.RS
.nf
echo \(dq$PW\(dq | stegx decode \-i out.png \\
      \-\-password\-stdin \-\-stdout | ssh\-add \-
.fi
.RE
.PP
3\-of\-5 Shamir split and recovery:
.RS
.nf
stegx shamir\-split   \-k 3 \-n 5 \-f secret.bin \\
      \-c c1.png c2.png c3.png c4.png c5.png \-O shares/
stegx shamir\-combine \-i shares/stego_share_01.png \\
                     shares/stego_share_02.png \\
                     shares/stego_share_03.png \\
      \-d ./out \-o recovered.bin
.fi
.RE

