.SH SECURITY
.B stegx
is designed to protect data at rest inside an image file. It is
\fInot\fR a vulnerability scanner, a malware tool, or a command and
control channel. In particular:
.IP \(bu 2
Passwords are read from a TTY via \fBgetpass\fR(3) by default.
Passing \fB\-p\fR leaks the password to shell history and to
\fBps\fR(1).
.IP \(bu
Wrong password, wrong keyfile and non\-StegX input all produce the
same generic error. Do not parse the error text.
.IP \(bu
The key hierarchy runs the password through Argon2id (default
\fItime=3, memory=64\ MiB, parallelism=4\fR) before HKDF\-deriving
sub\-keys. Expect decoding to take roughly one Argon2id invocation
(~1\ s on a modern machine).
.IP \(bu
The container header is authenticated as AEAD associated data;
tampering with any flag, salt or nonce invalidates the GCM tag.
.IP \(bu
LSB matching (+/-1) is used by default to resist chi\-square / RS
analysis. Matrix embedding and adaptive cost\-map filtering can be
enabled for stronger resistance to CNN\-based steganalysers at a
bandwidth cost.

